cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.NA 

This paper deals with image denoising, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithm involves a variational approach, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT). The use of sparsity and self-similarity in natural images is also a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the optimization technique used in the algorithm is based on the Split-Bregman method, which is a common numerical analysis technique (cs.NA).
